# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: BlackMonolith | Scene: TheBlackMonolithWarrior4
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah does not wander into her dreams, she is dragged into them."
    new "Sarah does not wander into her dreams, she is dragged into them."

    old "The darkness rises up around her as she sinks deeper into the void."
    new "The darkness rises up around her as she sinks deeper into the void."

    old "Her feet are sundered from the earth, her hands slip from the edges of the bed."
    new "Her feet are sundered from the earth, her hands slip from the edges of the bed."

    old "Amid an ocean of blackness, she floats."
    new "Amid an ocean of blackness, she floats."

    old "Slowly, Sarah opens her eyes and sees the pit."
    new "Slowly, Sarah opens her eyes and sees the pit."

    old "Thoughts come to her mind, but she knows them to be strange. They are not her own."
    new "Thoughts come to her mind, but she knows them to be strange. They are not her own."

    old "Still she thinks them."
    new "Still she thinks them."

    old "There is no reference. No above and now below. Sarah turns her head aside."
    new "There is no reference. No above and now below. Sarah turns her head aside."

    old "Observing, she sees the solid black give way to texture."
    new "Observing, she sees the solid black give way to texture."

    old "It's not a void, she realizes. Amid the blackness, a dark mass writhes, twists and curls."
    new "It's not a void, she realizes. Amid the blackness, a dark mass writhes, twists and curls."

    old "She doesn't feel afraid."
    new "She doesn't feel afraid."

    old "A voice rises up towards her."
    new "A voice rises up towards her."

    old "Voice\" \"You are close, Sarah."
    new "Voice\" \"You are close, Sarah."

    old "Where are you?"
    new "Where are you?"

    old "Voice\" \"You know where I am."
    new "Voice\" \"You know where I am."

    old "The dig site."
    new "The dig site."

    old "Voice\" \"Do not delay further. No more secrets."
    new "Voice\" \"Do not delay further. No more secrets."

    old "The voice feels familiar."
    new "The voice feels familiar."

    old "As violently as the dream came to her, so violently it departs."
    new "As violently as the dream came to her, so violently it departs."

    old "Sarah shoots awake, her body drenched in cold sweat."
    new "Sarah shoots awake, her body drenched in cold sweat."

    old "She frantically reaches around, feeling solid ground beneath her body, under her touch, she slowly grounds herself."
    new "She frantically reaches around, feeling solid ground beneath her body, under her touch, she slowly grounds herself."

    old "She feels her chest rise and fall, slowing with each breath as she calms back down."
    new "She feels her chest rise and fall, slowing with each breath as she calms back down."

    old "Sarah takes to her work, hoping for a distraction from the dreams."
    new "Sarah takes to her work, hoping for a distraction from the dreams."

    old "Yet, in the back of her mind, the dream and its beckoning voice are never far way."
    new "Yet, in the back of her mind, the dream and its beckoning voice are never far way."

    old "After a long morning of meetings, nearly drawing into the afternoon, Sarah had finally managed to find some time to herself."
    new "After a long morning of meetings, nearly drawing into the afternoon, Sarah had finally managed to find some time to herself."

    old "Exploring the ruined city on Nauyziri, she made her way down the stretched out roads that all ran towards the city center."
    new "Exploring the ruined city on Nauyziri, she made her way down the stretched out roads that all ran towards the city center."

    old "Everywhere, signs of the decay were evident."
    new "Everywhere, signs of the decay were evident."

    old "But it was different than in Bagrad."
    new "But it was different than in Bagrad."

    old "Where Bagrad had been a city dying, this was a city long dead. The remaining ruins defied the last advances of the desert."
    new "Where Bagrad had been a city dying, this was a city long dead. The remaining ruins defied the last advances of the desert."

    old "The people had been driven out, and in time, so too would the last reminders that they had ever been here."
    new "The people had been driven out, and in time, so too would the last reminders that they had ever been here."

    old "Overhead, the desert sun loomd mercilessly."
    new "Overhead, the desert sun loomd mercilessly."

    old "Sarah strode up along one of the roads."
    new "Sarah strode up along one of the roads."

    old "As she came closer to the city center, the amount of Mythran soldiers intensified."
    new "As she came closer to the city center, the amount of Mythran soldiers intensified."

    old "Still, they paid her little attention."
    new "Still, they paid her little attention."

    old "With little real danger other than the occasional raid by the tribesmen, the soldiers had adopted a lackadaisical attitude."
    new "With little real danger other than the occasional raid by the tribesmen, the soldiers had adopted a lackadaisical attitude."

    old "But as she passed by the soldiers, she also began to realize that it wasn't just soldiers."
    new "But as she passed by the soldiers, she also began to realize that it wasn't just soldiers."

    old "Here, near the center of the city, she began to see differing groups of people."
    new "Here, near the center of the city, she began to see differing groups of people."

    old "The uniforms of soldiers began to become interspersed with the robes of scholars, merchants."
    new "The uniforms of soldiers began to become interspersed with the robes of scholars, merchants."

    old "As she reached the top of the hill, she could see out across the heart of the city."
    new "As she reached the top of the hill, she could see out across the heart of the city."

    old "A large hole in the earth, as if someone had plunged a dagger into the flesh of the earth and rended it open."
    new "A large hole in the earth, as if someone had plunged a dagger into the flesh of the earth and rended it open."

    old "The archeological excavation."
    new "The archeological excavation."

    old "Sprawled out across the dig site, countless people working. From far away, they looked like ants crawling across an ant hill."
    new "Sprawled out across the dig site, countless people working. From far away, they looked like ants crawling across an ant hill."

    old "This was what had motivated the Mythrans to come all the way out here."
    new "This was what had motivated the Mythrans to come all the way out here."

    old "Lady Carolyn had suggested their interests were only historical, but Sarah doubted their objectives were quite so selfless."
    new "Lady Carolyn had suggested their interests were only historical, but Sarah doubted their objectives were quite so selfless."

    old "As Sarah drew nearer, she could feel something pulling on her, urging her onward."
    new "As Sarah drew nearer, she could feel something pulling on her, urging her onward."

    old "She continued walking towards the dig site, walking down curving paths, constructed scaffolding."
    new "She continued walking towards the dig site, walking down curving paths, constructed scaffolding."

    old "More and more, around her, the throngs of archeologists and researchers, hard at work."
    new "More and more, around her, the throngs of archeologists and researchers, hard at work."

    old "She could see their eyes drift towards her, her soldier's appearance a rarity here."
    new "She could see their eyes drift towards her, her soldier's appearance a rarity here."

    old "Her feet guided her along a path she hadn't known."
    new "Her feet guided her along a path she hadn't known."

    old "She awakes to find herself near one of the ledges."
    new "She awakes to find herself near one of the ledges."

    old "Beneath her, the ever descending depths of the pit."
    new "Beneath her, the ever descending depths of the pit."

    old "As she looks into it, her attention on it sharpens. She fixates and obsesses over the thing, until she finds she can no longer look away."
    new "As she looks into it, her attention on it sharpens. She fixates and obsesses over the thing, until she finds she can no longer look away."

    old "Only when a scream rings out, does she awake to herself."
    new "Only when a scream rings out, does she awake to herself."

    old "For a moment, she cannot understand where the scream is coming from, or why."
    new "For a moment, she cannot understand where the scream is coming from, or why."

    old "Then she feels the motions of her body, the air rushing past her face, the vertigo seizing her mind and the knot forming in her stomach."
    new "Then she feels the motions of her body, the air rushing past her face, the vertigo seizing her mind and the knot forming in her stomach."

    old "She is falling."
    new "She is falling."

    old "The earth rushes up towardsh her and Sarah closes her eyes."
    new "The earth rushes up towardsh her and Sarah closes her eyes."

    old "She is surprised at how calm she feels in the face of death."
    new "She is surprised at how calm she feels in the face of death."

    old "For a moment, the world goes dark around her."
    new "For a moment, the world goes dark around her."

    old "So she suspects for a moment, but Sarah knows this cannot be it."
    new "So she suspects for a moment, but Sarah knows this cannot be it."

    old "She can feel the ache in her body. The sand and gravel against her skin."
    new "She can feel the ache in her body. The sand and gravel against her skin."

    old "Perhaps the dead still think, but surely they don't suffer the minor annoyances of the living."
    new "Perhaps the dead still think, but surely they don't suffer the minor annoyances of the living."

    old "Sarah opens her eyes and finds herself laying on the floor."
    new "Sarah opens her eyes and finds herself laying on the floor."

    old "Earth is all around her, but it takes her a moment longer to realize that it's a tunnel."
    new "Earth is all around her, but it takes her a moment longer to realize that it's a tunnel."

    old "Sarah plants her hands on the ground and pushes herself up, back to her feet."
    new "Sarah plants her hands on the ground and pushes herself up, back to her feet."

    old "She checks herself for injuries but finds none."
    new "She checks herself for injuries but finds none."

    old "None that one would have expected, given the height of the fall."
    new "None that one would have expected, given the height of the fall."

    old "As she turns her head, she finds the tunnel solid. How she ended up in it, she can't remember."
    new "As she turns her head, she finds the tunnel solid. How she ended up in it, she can't remember."

    old "Much less, she can explain how she can see anything at all."
    new "Much less, she can explain how she can see anything at all."

    old "Despite the tunnel being like a tomb, there is a light here."
    new "Despite the tunnel being like a tomb, there is a light here."

    old "As she orients herself, Sarah sees the tunnel leading out ahead of her."
    new "As she orients herself, Sarah sees the tunnel leading out ahead of her."

    old "The source of the light, whatever it is, just beyond the bend."
    new "The source of the light, whatever it is, just beyond the bend."

    old "She places her hands against the walls of the cave for balance as she begins to move forward."
    new "She places her hands against the walls of the cave for balance as she begins to move forward."

    old "The space is surprisingly soundless, only the sound of rocks scratching against her mailed boots can be heard."
    new "The space is surprisingly soundless, only the sound of rocks scratching against her mailed boots can be heard."

    old "She follows the tunnel for a short while until it suddenly turns and opens up."
    new "She follows the tunnel for a short while until it suddenly turns and opens up."

    old "Where the tunnel was sparse in light and anything but earth, this room is the opposite."
    new "Where the tunnel was sparse in light and anything but earth, this room is the opposite."

    old "At first, the many stimuli overpower her, it's hard to make out anything."
    new "At first, the many stimuli overpower her, it's hard to make out anything."

    old "Slowly, her eyes adjust and she begins to understand what she is looking at."
    new "Slowly, her eyes adjust and she begins to understand what she is looking at."

    old "The room reaches up high and far."
    new "The room reaches up high and far."

    old "Still beneath the earth, a ceiling of dirt blocking out anything above her."
    new "Still beneath the earth, a ceiling of dirt blocking out anything above her."

    old "Yet, this place is oddly full of life."
    new "Yet, this place is oddly full of life."

    old "Vegetation in many colours grows all along the sides of the cave. Strange and unique species that she has never seen."
    new "Vegetation in many colours grows all along the sides of the cave. Strange and unique species that she has never seen."

    old "A small river courses through the side of it."
    new "A small river courses through the side of it."

    old "Water is a rarity in this place, much less a flowing river."
    new "Water is a rarity in this place, much less a flowing river."

    old "As Sarah walks further into the room, she can feel the humidity in the air, so heavy she can feel it on her lungs."
    new "As Sarah walks further into the room, she can feel the humidity in the air, so heavy she can feel it on her lungs."

    old "Suddenly, the sounds of grinding rock vanishes, and she hears her own footsteps being muted."
    new "Suddenly, the sounds of grinding rock vanishes, and she hears her own footsteps being muted."

    old "Looking down, she sees grass beneath her feet."
    new "Looking down, she sees grass beneath her feet."

    old "The more she looks, the more the whole space feels to her like a garden of some kind."
    new "The more she looks, the more the whole space feels to her like a garden of some kind."

    old "Sarah takes off one of her mailed gloves and places her hands against the grass."
    new "Sarah takes off one of her mailed gloves and places her hands against the grass."

    old "Damp and soft, pleasing to the touch."
    new "Damp and soft, pleasing to the touch."

    old "She is touching it, if only to convince herself it's real."
    new "She is touching it, if only to convince herself it's real."

    old "As she turns her head away from the grass and takes in the room, she is suddenly struck by the sight of it."
    new "As she turns her head away from the grass and takes in the room, she is suddenly struck by the sight of it."

    old "Her eyes transfixed on it, she finds herself forgetting about the grass."
    new "Her eyes transfixed on it, she finds herself forgetting about the grass."

    old "Standing near the center of the room, a massive black monolith looms over everything else."
    new "Standing near the center of the room, a massive black monolith looms over everything else."

    old "It reaches so high, it nearly touches the ceiling of the cave."
    new "It reaches so high, it nearly touches the ceiling of the cave."

    old "The object stands in the room, but seems oddly detached from it. Alien to the space around it."
    new "The object stands in the room, but seems oddly detached from it. Alien to the space around it."

    old "Air around it softly vibrates."
    new "Air around it softly vibrates."

    old "Voice\" \"Finally, we meet in truth, Sarah."
    new "Voice\" \"Finally, we meet in truth, Sarah."

    old "Sarah stands up and walks closer towards the thing. Her steps are measured and careful, hestitant."
    new "Sarah stands up and walks closer towards the thing. Her steps are measured and careful, hestitant."

    old "Who are you..."
    new "Who are you..."

    old "She speaks the words softly, as if fearing the response."
    new "She speaks the words softly, as if fearing the response."

    old "Voice\" \"We have met before, and before that and before that. Again and again we meet. In many lives. But always we end up here."
    new "Voice\" \"We have met before, and before that and before that. Again and again we meet. In many lives. But always we end up here."

    old "Sarah watches as a black smoke rises up around the monolith, and slowly the miasma grows solid and takes form."
    new "Sarah watches as a black smoke rises up around the monolith, and slowly the miasma grows solid and takes form."

    old "The last of it to take shape, the familiar face-mask that she has seen only once before in her life."
    new "The last of it to take shape, the familiar face-mask that she has seen only once before in her life."

    old "You...you're that spirit from Bagrad."
    new "You...you're that spirit from Bagrad."

    old "The creature looks similar to before, but now appearing many times larger in size."
    new "The creature looks similar to before, but now appearing many times larger in size."

    old "Voice\" \"Yes, but I address you by your name and so you may call me by mine. I am Razaphel."
    new "Voice\" \"Yes, but I address you by your name and so you may call me by mine. I am Razaphel."

    old "Razaphel..."
    new "Razaphel..."

    old "Often have I dreamed of this moment, and often do I dream of it still."
    new "Often have I dreamed of this moment, and often do I dream of it still."

    old "To be in this moment, feels strange to me."
    new "To be in this moment, feels strange to me."

    old "Sarah frowns as she observes the spirit twisting around the black monolith. It appears attached to it, or emerging from it."
    new "Sarah frowns as she observes the spirit twisting around the black monolith. It appears attached to it, or emerging from it."

    old "Are you the voice that I have been hearing? Playing with my mind?"
    new "Are you the voice that I have been hearing? Playing with my mind?"

    old "For a moment, there is only silence."
    new "For a moment, there is only silence."

    old "I will speak only truth from now on, Sarah. I will admit to my deceit, and ask for your forgiveness."
    new "I will speak only truth from now on, Sarah. I will admit to my deceit, and ask for your forgiveness."

    old "I had almost begun to believe myself mad."
    new "I had almost begun to believe myself mad."

    old "She stares at the impossible creature."
    new "She stares at the impossible creature."

    old "Perhaps I still am."
    new "Perhaps I still am."

    old "I promise you, you are not mad, daughter-of-starlight."
    new "I promise you, you are not mad, daughter-of-starlight."

    old "Long have I hoped to meet you here, and now to see you before me, I find my courage failing me."
    new "Long have I hoped to meet you here, and now to see you before me, I find my courage failing me."

    old "Another pause lingers between them."
    new "Another pause lingers between them."

    old "Speak, creature. Whatever words you have for me, spill them now. Tell me why you brought me here."
    new "Speak, creature. Whatever words you have for me, spill them now. Tell me why you brought me here."

    old "I brought you here to save you. And in turn, I pray that you might save me."
    new "I brought you here to save you. And in turn, I pray that you might save me."

    old "Sarah walked closer towards the monolith. She oddly felt no fear of it."
    new "Sarah walked closer towards the monolith. She oddly felt no fear of it."

    old "I need no saving. Tell me why I am here, or I will dig my way out of this place and bring the earth down on top of you."
    new "I need no saving. Tell me why I am here, or I will dig my way out of this place and bring the earth down on top of you."

    old "The creature suddenly hissed. Was it laughter or fear, it sounded close enough to be either."
    new "The creature suddenly hissed. Was it laughter or fear, it sounded close enough to be either."

    old "I shall speak, but first, permit me to tell you a story."
    new "I shall speak, but first, permit me to tell you a story."

    old "Tell me then, spirit. But only truth."
    new "Tell me then, spirit. But only truth."

    old "Many millenia ago, this world was home not to the many empires and kingdoms that exist today, but only a single empire."
    new "Many millenia ago, this world was home not to the many empires and kingdoms that exist today, but only a single empire."

    old "It stretched across the surface of the world and all peoples of this world fell under it."
    new "It stretched across the surface of the world and all peoples of this world fell under it."

    old "The world looked very different from how it does now, and the Gods of your world walked freely and spoke in plain voices."
    new "The world looked very different from how it does now, and the Gods of your world walked freely and spoke in plain voices."

    old "The Gods? They are only a fiction, stories to keep children from misbehaving."
    new "The Gods? They are only a fiction, stories to keep children from misbehaving."

    old "Today, yes, but once they walked the surface of your world as casually as one might witness a mountain."
    new "Today, yes, but once they walked the surface of your world as casually as one might witness a mountain."

    old "In this empire of old, your race communed with the Pantheon and they guided you from savagery to civilization."
    new "In this empire of old, your race communed with the Pantheon and they guided you from savagery to civilization."

    old "From the dawn of your race and for many millenia after, such was the only way the world was."
    new "From the dawn of your race and for many millenia after, such was the only way the world was."

    old "Countless generations, birthed and died, as the progress of your species crawled on."
    new "Countless generations, birthed and died, as the progress of your species crawled on."

    old "All of this, until under Empress Ayamari, this empire reached its zenith."
    new "All of this, until under Empress Ayamari, this empire reached its zenith."

    old "She ruled as the best of your people, the paragon of your race. Under her, the people flourished."
    new "She ruled as the best of your people, the paragon of your race. Under her, the people flourished."

    old "All who saw her, beautiful and righteous, praised her."
    new "All who saw her, beautiful and righteous, praised her."

    old "All wished for the same thing that she wished for in her heart, that she might live and rule forever."
    new "All wished for the same thing that she wished for in her heart, that she might live and rule forever."

    old "As the years dragged on and her body slowly faded, this Empress knew her hour would soon pass."
    new "As the years dragged on and her body slowly faded, this Empress knew her hour would soon pass."

    old "She feared for her own life, yes, but more than that she feared for her people, who might again fall subject to imperfect rulers."
    new "She feared for her own life, yes, but more than that she feared for her people, who might again fall subject to imperfect rulers."

    old "Sarah listened intently as the spirit continued to speak."
    new "Sarah listened intently as the spirit continued to speak."

    old "In desperation, she reached out to the Gods of your Pantheon and begged them to give her more life."
    new "In desperation, she reached out to the Gods of your Pantheon and begged them to give her more life."

    old "But though they favored her as well, they refused."
    new "But though they favored her as well, they refused."

    old "Your Gods were proud and arrogant, and immortality was the privilege of Gods, not mortals."
    new "Your Gods were proud and arrogant, and immortality was the privilege of Gods, not mortals."

    old "Denied, but still desperate, the Empress had men scour the earth for means of extending her life, but found nothing."
    new "Denied, but still desperate, the Empress had men scour the earth for means of extending her life, but found nothing."

    old "It was in her darkest hour when a thought came to her."
    new "It was in her darkest hour when a thought came to her."

    old "Perhaps these Gods might have denied her, but what if there were others Gods out there? Some who might look favorably on her request?"
    new "Perhaps these Gods might have denied her, but what if there were others Gods out there? Some who might look favorably on her request?"

    old "A skilled magician in her own right, the Empress and her order of mages researched this new path until they finally discovered something."
    new "A skilled magician in her own right, the Empress and her order of mages researched this new path until they finally discovered something."

    old "A different world, in a place beyond the dimensions of your own, where life lived forever."
    new "A different world, in a place beyond the dimensions of your own, where life lived forever."

    old "Eternal life. Gods. Sarah sought to make sense of it all."
    new "Eternal life. Gods. Sarah sought to make sense of it all."

    old "They prepared a ritual which they believed would allow the Empress to reach out to this new world and contact their Gods."
    new "They prepared a ritual which they believed would allow the Empress to reach out to this new world and contact their Gods."

    old "After months of preparation, the ritual was carried out and the other world was summoned into this one."
    new "After months of preparation, the ritual was carried out and the other world was summoned into this one."

    old "But the spell did not stay true."
    new "But the spell did not stay true."

    old "This other world was summoned, but all of existence covers all of existence."
    new "This other world was summoned, but all of existence covers all of existence."

    old "There is no space for two worlds, in one world."
    new "There is no space for two worlds, in one world."

    old "And so, your plane of existence collapsed onto this other world which had been summoned, trapping their existence underneath yours."
    new "And so, your plane of existence collapsed onto this other world which had been summoned, trapping their existence underneath yours."

    old "Sarah could feel her mind racing."
    new "Sarah could feel her mind racing."

    old "So much of it seemed like madness, and yet, she found it equally hard to imagine the spirit having made all of it up."
    new "So much of it seemed like madness, and yet, she found it equally hard to imagine the spirit having made all of it up."

    old "How can it be that I have never heard of any of this?"
    new "How can it be that I have never heard of any of this?"

    old "When the worlds smashed into each other, countless violent rifts formed across the world as my race poured into your world."
    new "When the worlds smashed into each other, countless violent rifts formed across the world as my race poured into your world."

    old "A great war raged between your race and mine. Between your Gods and mine."
    new "A great war raged between your race and mine. Between your Gods and mine."

    old "In the end, we were driven back and the gates were sealed up, trapping us beneath the reality of your world."
    new "In the end, we were driven back and the gates were sealed up, trapping us beneath the reality of your world."

    old "The spirit's choice of words alerted her."
    new "The spirit's choice of words alerted her."

    old "Your world..."
    new "Your world..."

    old "Do you mean that...you are a creature of this other world."
    new "Do you mean that...you are a creature of this other world."

    old "For a moment, silence."
    new "For a moment, silence."

    old "The spirit's voice seemed distant."
    new "The spirit's voice seemed distant."

    old "In my own world, my form was much different from the one you see before you."
    new "In my own world, my form was much different from the one you see before you."

    old "Only be stealing myself across the divide between the worlds, before the gates were sealed, did I manage to remain on this side."
    new "Only be stealing myself across the divide between the worlds, before the gates were sealed, did I manage to remain on this side."

